SIMPLE: eponyme
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eponyme
<hw>Ep"o*nyme</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧ponyme</ets>. See
<er>Eponymous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The hypothetical individual
who is assumed as the person from whom any race, city, etc., took its
name; <as>as, Hellen is an <ex>eponym</ex> of the
Hellenes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A name, as of a people, country, and the like,
derived from that of an individual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eponymic</ent>⟦br⟧
